      <h3>Contributions</h3>
				<p>Contributed to the development of nursing as a true profession and inspired the first professional school of nursing</p>

<p>Developed the modern hospital including architecture, organizational charts, medical records, infection control, patient education, and nutritional services</p>

<p>Invented statistical diagrams to report the first hospital epidemiological study showing how basic sanitation reduced death rates</p>

<p>Wrote "Notes on Nursing" which is cited as one of the most influential books in the history of health care</p>

<p>Changed society's view on nursing, which had been looked down on by the upper classes, as her notoriety and efforts resulted in it being considered an honorable profession
</p>
